                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2976: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shaw</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-01T17:00:00+00:00"
                            >December 1, 1931—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 1—1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>825. From Ambassador Dawes: Referring to Department’s No. 609 of November
                        30.<note n="32" xml:id="d564fn32">Not printed.</note> The Italian
                    representative called upon me this noon in regard to a delegate of his country
                    joining the commission, and I informed Scialoja in the Under Secretary’s words
                    that my Government would naturally not object to an Italian member on the
                    commission, since its appointment is entirely a League of Nations matter.
                    [Dawes.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Shaw</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
